To compile libdvdnav for Windows follow the steps below, note that for Linux the
libdvdnav4-dev package should be installed instead.

- Make sure MSYS is installed in the same directory as the QtSDK mingw
  installation and start a bash shell.

- Configure dlfcn using:
  ./configure --enable-static

- Run mingw32-make and copy libdl.a to ext/dvdnav/bin.win32.

- Configure libdvdread using:
  ./configure2 --enable-static --disable-shared --extra-cflags="-I../../dlfcn-win32-r19/ -march=i686 -mmmx -msse -msse2 -mfpmath=sse"
  Ignore the error "./configure2: line 95: cd: /usr/local/: No such file or directory"

- Run mingw32-make and copy obj/libdvdread.a to ext/dvdnav/bin.win32.

- In the libdvdread source tree; make a copy of the src directory and name it "dvdread".
 
- In the libdvdnav source tree; open the "configure2" file and comment out lines 106-114.
 
- Configure libdvdnav using:
  ./configure2 --enable-static --disable-shared --extra-cflags="-I../../libdvdread-4.1.3/ -march=i686 -mmmx -msse -msse2 -mfpmath=sse"
  Ignore the error "./configure2: line 100: cd: /usr/local/: No such file or directory"

- Run mingw32-make and copy obj/libdvdnav.a to ext/dvdnav/bin.win32.
